South Africa’s President Cyril Ramaphosa said on Wednesday the cabinet will discuss self-generation of energy on Friday, after power utility Eskom this week implemented severe power cuts that dealt a further blow to an ailing economy. Read: Power crisis eases after Eskom rushes to fix plants Eskom will work to restore network stability by end of March – Ramaphosa “Right now a clear proposal has been put on the table, and there are a number of applications from the private sector which has been saying it wants to self-generate,” Ramaphosa told journalists. “In the end what they don’t use they will be able to put or sell into the grid. …So that is a matter that is now going to be discussed at the cabinet on Friday.”